headline: Why MicroStrategy (MSTR) Stock Is Trading Up Today
summary: Shares of business analytics software company MicroStrategy (NASDAQ:MSTR) jumped 3% in the morning session after the price of Bitcoin surged to a new record high, surpassing $118,000. As the world's largest corporate holder of Bitcoin, MicroStrategy's stock price is highly sensitive to the cryptocurrency's market movements. This significant unrealized gain on its digital asset holdings is providing a strong tailwind for the stock.
